<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1193,1518]" box="[197,1245,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,357,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widespread in the Palearctic region (
<bibRefCitation author="Skoracka" box="[796,1050,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="Skoracka, A., Lewandowski, M. &amp; Boczek, J. (2005) A catalogue of eriophyoid mites (Acari: Eriophoidea) of Poland. Catalogus faunae Poloniae, Natura optima dux Foundation, Warszawa, Poland, 199 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Skoracka 
<emphasis box="[915,974,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[988,1050,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; de 
<bibRefCitation author="Lillo" box="[1097,1233,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="de Lillo, E. (2004) Fauna Europaea: Eriophyoidea. In: W. Magowski (ed.) Fauna Europaea: Acariformes. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, http: // www. faunaeur. org" type="book" year="2004">
Lillo, 
<number box="[1169,1233,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1193,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,446,1305,1331]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">Relation to the host.</emphasis>
Gall-making: it causes irregularly shaped pustules raised on both leaf surfaces, often reddish on the upper side, yellow-green on the under side with an oval opening.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1193,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">
